File: Sibanye-Stillwater Elizabeth Sejake/Gallo Images/City Press JOHANNESBURG - Sibanye-Stillwater has received accreditation to administer COVID-19 vaccines.
In preparation for launching its own COVID-19 initiative earlier this year, the mining giant applied for accreditation to administer COVID-19 vaccines at four facilities at its gold and PGM operations in South Africa. READ:Â COVID-19 vaccine: Sibanye-Stillwater to contribute R200m They include Marikana in the North West, Libanon, and Driefontein in Gauteng, and Beatrix in the Free State. The company now stands ready to assist the government further with the wider roll-out of vaccines to employees, families of employees, and surrounding communities.